    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Yes im using 2 instances of instantsearch.\nthen in one instance of of them , i implement the searchFunction(helper) like this :\n\n``` javascript\nsearchFunction: function(helper) {\nvar query = companiesSearch.helper.state.query;\nprojectsSearch.helper.setQuery(query);\nprojectsSearch.helper.search();\nhelper.search();\n}\n```\n\nRegarding my index switch, im using a simple form select with 2 options representing my index and then i switch and render the layout accordingly to the selected index using the same input type search, shared by the 2 instances of instantsearch.\n",
