  {
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Hi @bobylito \r\n\r\nI looked at the [documentation link you provided - `options.urlSync`](https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/documentation/#initialization), but couldn't tell, hence asking here.\r\n\r\nIs it possible to implement this in a static site also? I have a static hugo site - [pawpurrazi.com](https://www.pawpurrazi.com/) - hosted on Netlify and am exploring search options for this, and Algolia was recommended.\r\n\r\nI want to be able to display a search screen and allow user to select tags and/or categories from it. Once a user clicks search, I was the search parameters to be in the URL, so that if they bookmark it and revisit the query will be re-executed.\r\n\r\nExample: If user puts \"cat videos\" in search box, which would eventually lead to [some of the videos listed here](https://www.pawpurrazi.com/tags/cat-videos/) , the URL should have something like https://www.pawpurrazi.com/search?q=cat%20videos and if they click this url again, the search should be re-executed and results displayed.\r\n\r\nThank you!",
